  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200&deg;C/ 180&deg;C (fan)/ 400&deg;F/ Gas 6</p>\r\n<p>Cut narrow slices (about the width of a pound coin) into the skin of the <strong>waxy</strong>&nbsp;<strong>potatoes</strong>, making sure not to cut all the way down to the base - these are your <strong>hasselback</strong> <strong>potatoes</strong></p>\r\n<p>Tip: rest the potatoes on to a wooden spoon when cutting, it will prevent you from cutting all the way through the potato!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/833.step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/833.step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/833.step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/833.step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/833.step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>hasselback&nbsp;</strong><strong>potatoes</strong> to an oven tray (use <strong>tin foil</strong> to avoid mess!), drizzle each with <strong>olive oil</strong> and season with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>\r\n<p>Place in the oven for 30-35 min or until they're tender and starting to crisp</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/833.step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/833.step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/833.step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/833.step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/833.step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve 1/2<span class=\"text-danger\">&nbsp;[1]</span>&nbsp;<strong>vegetable</strong>&nbsp;<strong>stock cube</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water </strong>in a measuring jug</p>\r\n<p>Add 15g <span class=\"text-danger\">[30g]</span>&nbsp;<strong>butter</strong> to a pot over a medium heat</p>\r\n<p>Once melted, add 15g <span class=\"text-danger\">[30g]</span>&nbsp;<strong>flour</strong> and stir for 2-3 min until a sandy coloured paste is formed - this is your<strong> roux</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/833.step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/833.step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/833.step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/833.step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/833.step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>Shaoxing</strong><strong> wine</strong> to the <strong>roux</strong> and cook for 30 sec</p>\r\n<p>Stir the <strong>vegetable&nbsp;stock</strong> gradually into the <strong>roux&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Whisk constantly for 5 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>clotted cream</strong>, season with <strong>pepper</strong> and remove from the heat - this is your&nbsp;<strong>velout&eacute; sauce</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/833.step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/833.step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/833.step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/833.step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/833.step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Trim, then chop each <strong>spring onions</strong> in half&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Chop the <strong>chives</strong> finely</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/833__step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/833__step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/833__step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/833__step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/833__step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>&nbsp;over a medium-high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>spring onions</strong> and <strong>T</strong><strong>enderstem broccoli&nbsp;</strong>with a generous pinch of&nbsp;<strong>salt</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cook for 5 min or until the <strong>spring onions</strong> are starting to caramelise, then transfer the vegetables to a sheet of <strong>tin foil</strong>&nbsp;&amp; wrap to seal the package</p>\r\n<p>Put the foil package in the oven until serving&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/833__step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/833__step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/833__step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/833__step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/833__step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the same pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p>\r\n<p>Pat the&nbsp;<strong>sea bass</strong>&nbsp;dry and season the skin generously with <strong>salt</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once the pan is hot, place the <strong>sea bass</strong>, skin-side down, and cook for 4 min, then flip the sea bass and cook for a further 1 min</p>\r\n<p>Tip: try not to move the fish around the pan, as this will prevent it from crisping up</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/833.step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/833.step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/833.step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/833.step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/833.step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the <strong>velout&eacute; sauce</strong> to a medium heat for 1 min to warm through and stir in the <strong>chopped&nbsp;</strong><strong>chives</strong></p>\r\n<p>Serve the <strong>sea bass</strong> with the <strong>hasselback potatoes</strong>, <strong>vegetables</strong> and <strong>velout&eacute;&nbsp;sauce&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
